<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="55" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,426,612]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis box="[151,375,426,451]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">Material examined</emphasis>
: One specimen (
<number box="[579,624,426,452]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" value="303.0">303</number>
µm long) of unknown sex, collected at Lages do Pico, Pico Island, and mounted in Hoyer’s medium. The specific diagnosis is confirmed by the examination of a 
<typeStatus box="[1253,1354,466,492]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">paratype</typeStatus>
kindly loaned by the Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Verona.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,426,612]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">
The species is recorded from Europe, North 
<collectingCountry box="[724,825,546,572]" name="United States of America" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">America</collectingCountry>
and probably 
<collectingCountry box="[995,1065,546,572]" name="Japan" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">Japan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1077,1224,546,572]" name="South Korea" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">South Korea</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1283,1373,546,572]" name="Taiwan" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
. This is the first record of this species in the Azores.
</paragraph>
